comment: Acyltransferase can use acyl-CoA of different acyl chain length and glucosamine free as UDP-glucosamine or bound to hpg4 of teicoplanin pseudoaglycone as substrates.

changelog.comment: Initial entry. Reviewer fixed composite SMILES and added a generic version of the reaction. Reviewer 1 added information from retired entry MITE0000036.
Fixed enzyme name to be more computer-readable.

reactions.description: Deacetylates N-acetylglucosaminyl residue on Hpg4 of the teicoplanin precursor.
Generic deacylation of a long chain fatty acid.

Substrate specificity is probably more general than depicted in the reaction SMARTS, but there is no precise information on substrate specificity. In order to avoid making the reaction too general, the complete backbone is included in the pattern.
Describes a deacylation of a C10 carboxylic acid. Probably only slow side reaction during teicoplanin biosynthesis.

Substrate specificity is probably more general than depicted in the reaction SMARTS, but there is no precise information on substrate specificity. In order to avoid making the reaction too general, the complete backbone is included in the pattern.
The highest catalytic efficiency of the enzyme is achieved with the glucosaminyl-teicoplanin pseudoaglycone as substrate.
Reaction does not occure naturally during teicoplanin biosynthesis; acyl-CoA as co-substrate.
